  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>BRC ASIA LIMITED We are a public-listed company that specialises in the manufacturing of steel prefabricated reinforcement for the construction industry. We are seeking suitably qualified personnel to join our team.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will support operations and HR by managing attendance records, coordinating employee leave and permits, assisting with training and event logistics, and maintaining office supplies and filing systems.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Update daily attendance records using Easytime and verify all supporting documents for medical, hospitalization, and annual leave to ensure accuracy</li><li>Login to E-leave portal to apply leave on behalf of the workers</li><li>Coordinate with HR and Works departments on employee home leave, resignation processes, and work permit or S-pass renewals to maintain compliance</li><li>Collaborate with HR and Works on scheduling and tracking worker training programs to support workforce development</li><li>Assist employees with applying for PSA Pass and Vehicle Pass, and update PSA expiry dates and contact numbers in the Master List for record accuracy</li><li>Prepare and distribute Notices of Infringement by scanning and forwarding them to relevant parties to ensure timely communication</li><li>Submit industrial accident reports provided by the WSH Officer to the relevant parties for further action</li><li>Collect boarding passes from workers returning from home leave and provide copies to HR for documentation</li><li>Support company events by assisting with planning and coordination to ensure smooth execution</li><li>Arrange company transport for workers to facilitate timely and safe travel</li><li>Supervise part-time cleaners to maintain cleanliness standards in the workplace</li><li>Manage office supplies including stationery, toiletries, and visitor beverages to ensure availability and orderliness</li><li>Organize and maintain filing systems to support efficient document retrieval and record keeping</li><li>Perform other ad hoc tasks or projects as assigned to support team needs</li></ul>",
